  "dateModified": "2026-04-27",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-27",
  "description": "The operating mode of liberalism in which platforms — digital platforms primarily, but also platform-style logics that have spread beyond software — become the primary medium of subject-formation, contradiction-management, and the distribution of feeling rules. Liberalism's central operations are no longer carried out by states, parties, churches, or schools as the dominant institutions; they are carried out by platforms, with the older institutions reorganizing around platform logics.",
  "name": "Platformal liberalism",
